The space between the words "cat" and "chased" would be labeled with an "O" tag, indicating that it is outside any named entity or other linguistic unit.The IOB format is commonly used in NLP tasks to identify and extract specific information from text, such as named entities, relationships, and dependencies. It is a simple and flexible format that can be used to represent a wide range of linguistic structures, and it is widely supported by many NLP tools and libraries.
